<TITLE> Huda, wife charged with 'car extortion' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Sunday charged former communications minister Barrister Nazmul Huda and wife Sigma Huda with taking a car in bribe from a businessman. Dhaka metropolitan sixth assistant sessions judge Shafiul Azam framed the charges against them in their presence. The accused pleaded innocent in court. The judge set Feb 14 to record testimonies in the case, filed by transport businessman GM Siraj on July 29, 2007 with Dhanmondi Police Station. Siraj, owner of Cab Express, said the then communications minister demanded two cars from him on Feb 23, 2003 to be used for the weekly "Khoborer Ontoraley" published by his wife. Huda threatened to shut his business after Siraj had expressed his inability to give him the cars. According to case details, on Feb 27, 2003, the businessman gave Huda a car worth Tk 3.95 lakh and promised to give the other later. The chargesheet was submitted in the case on Sep 28 last year. bdnew
